The Statue of Liberty will re-open on the Fourth of July, nearly eight months after the fierce winds and flooding caused damage to the island on which it stands.

When the ferocious hurricane hit late last October, Lady Liberty had only recently reopened following a $30million refurbishment.

But Liberty Island itself was badly damaged, with the floodwaters breaking railings, washing away paving stones, and destroying electrical systems. The statue remained unlit until the second week of November.

